Organics





Product Stewardship





Tsunami Debris Removal & Recycling











Recycling




Take the green approach. Reducing and reusing saves waste removal costs and helps protect our natural resources. That makes recycling the healthiest part of a waste management plan. Discover ways you can champion recycling in your community.


Organics
Organic waste typically comes from plant or animal products. A major advantage to this type of waste is that it’s biodegradable, which means there are plenty of green options for getting rid of it, like composting.

Learn more about organics

 
Product Stewardship
Taking ownership for the products we make and use is important. B.C. is a national leader in this regard – having industry arrange for the collection and recycling needed to manage the life cycle of designated products and packaging.

Learn more about product stewardship





Legislation & Regulations


The Recycling Regulation under authority of the Environmental Management Act sets out the requirements for Product Stewardship in B.C. In some cases, producers of designated products may appoint a stewardship agency to carry out their duties in accordance with an approved plan.



Environmental Management Act


Recycling Regulation





Waste Management Planning


Every municipality is responsible for its own waste management planning.



Learn more about the process





Where to Recycle?


Use the 'Recyclepedia' to find the right location to recycle specific materials or products.



Search for a location





